I'm Back Again!


Heres a post for all you no-lifers that get on here and read live journal like me whenever I'm on.


We play Alexandria this week at Alexandria. They're good but I think we'll win.


Other than that, a lot of things suck right now. Nothing goes right, or if it is, then it all of a sudden goes wrong.  I also don't like how a lot of things are right now. I hate it and I also miss some things and wish things could have just stayed the same and I dont understand why people and the way they are have changed. Yea I understand a lot of things are different because of certain things but just remember what it was you had before that change......That probably won't make any sense to some of you but maybe to someone.


I think I'm getting sick too. I can't breath, I keep coughing, and I don't feel good at all.

I also need to straighten back up and have God 1st in my life again!

Thats about all I can think of...

ATTENTION:
This is my once every few months post!


ROOOOLLLLLLLL TIDDEEEE RROOOLLLL!! The Alabama game was awesome except for Prothro getting hurt but they will still be good. they have a lot of talent this year.

Alabama will win the SEC.


Dora beat Montevallo other night 41 to 21. Another region win but next week is Chelsea. After the game me and valdez went over to Twilleys for a little while but I had to hurry up and leave.


Also, I can finally walk now without having a brace on but my knee still doesnt bend a lot.



Thats it..

I guess my junior year is good so far..I haven't been there enough to know yet. I haven't went a full day of school yet and now I can't even go until whenever??  For those of you that don't know, I tore my ACL and had to have surgery on it Thursday. I got hit in my knee and didnt think anything was wrong other than it being bruised very bad and just hurt a lot, but I knew it wasn't broke because I could still walk so I didnt tell anybody or the coaches and I went back out and had to go in motion on a play and as I was going in motion it gave out on me and snapped and I fell..Thats when I finished it off and tore it. But yea...Life is pretty boring right now. I can't do anything and it's killing me. Luckily people have came over and gave me some company lol and Thanks to all of the football team and cheerleaders for that huge card and all the candy and stuff and just everything and thanks to everybody else.  Dora also won Friday night at St. Clair County. I was there in my wheel chair lol and I cant wait for Thursday night against Cordova. Hopefully I can stand out there instead.. That's what I get to do all season lol. I cant play any.



I need the computer now hunter..come over

I'm pissed. It took $50 dollars to ALMOST fill up my truck!!!

Another thing that pisses me off is the HEAT!!!


But one thing I'm happy about is Tabitha comes to Dora tomorrow!!!

School's started back again and it's alright for now. All my classes are pretty good (I guess).   This summer has been the best summer yet! I did a lot of things with friends and just had a good time. I dont believe their was hardly ever a dull moment in the summer, other than when I was in bed.

Football season is about to start. We have a game on Thursday at St. Clair County and then after that is Game 1 against Cordova. We had a scrimmage game other night and we looked alright. I can't do anything right now because this year is sucking really bad for me so far in football. 1st I get a neck injury and I'm out for almost a week, then I come back & I'm able to hit again and I get a knee injury the first day I'm able to hit again. My knee was popped out place and possibly stretched or torn some ligaments in it. I have to go therapy now for a little while and on Monday for an MRI. Maybe when I'm able to play again I won't have anymore injuries the rest of the season. I also hope we have another perfect season and finally get past the 2nd round of the playoffs!!!

Another thing that's about to start is COLLEGE FOOTBALL!!!!! and I'm ready for that too.  Nothing like Alabama game days!  Maybe Alabama will do good this year too.

I'm ready for it to cool off also. I'm tired of this 90 and up degree weather with a humidity hotter than hell all the time. I hate the hot weather. I'm ready for fall!

I hate the end of the month when all of the Old people get their checks and make all their monthly stops to walmart, to eat, to the drug store, to fill up their cars, to buy groceries, and etc... As for the rest of the younger people, like me, all they do is severely piss me off and slow up everything for me. They think it's perfectly fine to pull out in front of me while I'm driving 60 mph and they are too afraid to go above 30 mph, which causes me to slam my brakes on and begin road rage as I pass them! Then once you pass them, It's fine for the old person to speed up then.

Another thing I hate is when I have to go get gas. Pumping the gas doesn't bother me at all but paying for it while their is 30 people in front of you and every one of them wants to buy a months supply of ciggaretes DOES! First of all, if the cashiers or clerks are going to keep the cigarettes with them, They need to know WHERE they are! People are on shedules, like me, and I'm having to wait on someone to kill thereselves before I can pay for my gas!

Another thing I dislike a lot is the fact that some people like to drive as close to people as possible and get as close to you as possible while stopped at a traffic light on a hill. I guess they've never heard of a 5 speed vehicle. Incase they've havent, well They ROLL sometimes just a little. Not a lot but but if sure feels better knowing that i have a foot or two incase I do roll, rather than an inch.

 

I'm sure there is a lot more things to add to this but this Is what I 've had to deal with today.

Tuesday morning I got up early and went to Tuscaloosa for cheer camp with Allisons mom and sister and we stayed there all day but it was great. Nothing better than being at a camp full of gurls everywhere. but then we got home late Tuesday night.

Friday I got up even earlier and went back to cheer camp with Allisons mom and watched them perform. They're pretty good this year! They won a lot.

Tomorrow I'm leavin to go to the beach and wont be back for a week. This will be another week of no workouts for me so I'm gonna be dieing of soreness when I get back to start football workouts!

I guess thats about it!

HAVE A GREAT LIFE!

I was at Lake Martin all weekend swimming, fishing, skiing, riding seadoos and whatever else I could find to do. It was great but it rained all day today but I still caught a lot of fish. Me and Caitlin McLeroy were there at the same time but we didnt know it.

Tomorrow I have to get up early and be at the school to go to the cheer camp with Allisons mom. That should be pretty good..Hundreds of babes every where!

Then I cut grass and went to work after that. After I got off work I went to Walmart and saw Rhonda then when Allison and Tieger got there Hunter Davis showed up and we went to his house.. and thats it for tonight! Im gone to sleep!
